import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

feature_columns = ['Pregnancies', 'Glucose', 'BloodPressure', 'SkinThickness', 'Insulin', 'BMI', 'DiabetesPedigreeFunction', 'Age', 'Outcome']

for feature in feature_columns:
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.histplot(df[feature], kde=True, bins=30, color='skyblue')
    plt.title(f'Distribution of {feature}')
    plt.xlabel(feature)
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
        
    skewness = df[feature].skew()
    if skewness > 0:
        skewness_type = 'positively skewed'
    elif skewness < 0:
        skewness_type = 'negatively skewed'
    else:
        skewness_type = 'approximately symmetric'
    
    print(f'{feature} skewness: {skewness} ({skewness_type})')
    
    plt.show()

Pregnancies skewness: 0.9016739791518588 (positively skewed)

Glucose skewness: 0.17375350179188992 (positively skewed)

BloodPressure skewness: -1.8436079833551302 (negatively skewed)

SkinThickness skewness: 0.10937249648187608 (positively skewed)

Insulin skewness: 2.272250858431574 (positively skewed)

BMI skewness: -0.42898158845356543 (negatively skewed)

DiabetesPedigreeFunction skewness: 1.919911066307204 (positively skewed)

Age skewness: 1.1295967011444805 (positively skewed)

Outcome skewness: 0.635016643444986 (positively skewed)

features = df.columns[:-1]

    ax.plot(df[feature])

In[39]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns


feature_columns = ['Pregnancies', 'Glucose', 'BloodPressure', 'SkinThickness', 'Insulin', 
                   'BMI', 'DiabetesPedigreeFunction', 'Age', 'Outcome']


for feature in feature_columns:
    if df[feature].nunique() < 10:  
        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
        sns.countplot(x=feature, data=df)
        plt.title(f'Bar Plot of {feature}')
        plt.xlabel(feature)
        plt.ylabel('Count')
        plt.show()


binary_features = ['Outcome']
for feature in binary_features:
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    df[feature].value_counts().plot.pie(autopct='%1.1f%%', colors=['skyblue', 'lightcoral'])
    plt.title(f'Pie Chart of {feature}')
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.show()
In[54]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns


plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 14})

for column in df.columns:
    if column != 'Outcome' and df[column].dtype == 'object':  
        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
        ax = df[column].value_counts().sort_index().plot(kind='bar', color='skyblue', width=0.7)
        plt.title(f'Distribution of {column}', fontsize=16)
        plt.xlabel(column, fontsize=14)
        plt.ylabel('Frequency', fontsize=14)

        
        ax.tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=12)
        
       
        for p in ax.patches:
            ax.annotate(f'{p.get_height()}', 
                        (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), 
                        ha='center', va='center', fontsize=12, color='black', 
                        xytext=(0, 5), textcoords='offset points')

        
        plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
        plt.tight_layout()  
        plt.show()


for column in df.columns:
    if column != 'Outcome' and df[column].dtype != 'object': 
        plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
        ax = df[column].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='skyblue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
        plt.title(f'Distribution of {column}', fontsize=16)
        plt.xlabel(column, fontsize=14)
        plt.ylabel('Frequency', fontsize=14)

        
        ax.tick_params(axis='both', which='major', labelsize=12)

        
        plt.tight_layout()  
        plt.show()


plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
ax = df['Outcome'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%', colors=['lightcoral', 'lightgreen'], fontsize=14)
plt.title('Distribution of Outcome', fontsize=16)
plt.ylabel('')  


plt.tight_layout()  
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Create a scatter plot for Age vs. Glucose Levels
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.scatterplot(x=df['Age'], y=df['Glucose'], hue=df['Outcome'], palette=['green', 'red'])
plt.title('Scatter Plot of Age vs. Glucose Levels')
plt.xlabel('Age')
plt.ylabel('Glucose Levels')
plt.legend(title='Outcome', labels=['No Diabetes', 'Diabetes'])
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
